      "writtenOn": "2026-03-16T03:07:39Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The Function* properties on Item.PCIeDevice (e.g. Function0DeviceId) are already marked as deprecated in phosphor-dbus-interfaces PCIeDevice.interface.yaml. The upstream intent is for providers to migrate to individual Item.PCIeFunction D-Bus objects instead.\n\nI also searched the dbus-sensors and entity-manager source trees and found no existing provider that sets these deprecated properties. So removing the old code path should not break any active machine.",
      "parentUuid": "86b8842a_9904706a",
      "revId": "e2c0a1dd1f0192633101ffbab1839d1636ff2c51",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "88e72f4c_abe4af8c",
        "filename": "/PATCHSET_LEVEL",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 0,
      "author": {
        "id": 1000020
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-03-17T20:04:07Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Can you do a search org wide? No docs, or other repos that use it ? \nJust want to double check we aren\u0027t breaking anyone. \n\nThis would be good to document in the commit msg",
      "parentUuid": "b9af4ccb_9733429f",
      "revId": "e2c0a1dd1f0192633101ffbab1839d1636ff2c51",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "b95431ba_96c3a240",
        "filename": "/PATCHSET_LEVEL",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 0,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002790
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-03-18T03:36:17Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Thanks for pushing on this. I did an org-wide search across all openbmc repositories.\n\npeci-pcie is the only repo that still uses the deprecated Function0* properties on Item.PCIeDevice. It dynamically sets properties like Function0VendorId, Function0DeviceId, Function0FunctionType, Function0DeviceClass, etc. via a loop over function numbers 0–7, and has no Item.PCIeFunction support. It was last updated in July 2025.\n\nAll other repos (dbus-sensors, pldm, entity-manager, smbios-mdr, phosphor-inventory-manager) either use only the non-deprecated properties (GenerationInUse, LanesInUse) or have no PCIe function inventory at all.\n\nSo if this patch removes the old Function0* code path, Intel machines using peci-pcie would lose PCIeFunction data in Redfish.\n\nHow would you like to proceed?",
      "parentUuid": "88e72f4c_abe4af8c",
      "revId": "e2c0a1dd1f0192633101ffbab1839d1636ff2c51",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "97d81478_7a4604ef",
        "filename": "/PATCHSET_LEVEL",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 0,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002790
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-03-18T05:35:30Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Alternatively, I could add backward compatibility: first search for Item.PCIeFunction objects (new interface); if none are found, fall back to iterating Function0\\*–Function7\\* properties on Item.PCIeDevice (old interface) and emit a warning log. This avoids needing to coordinate with a peci-pcie change. Would that be acceptable?",
      "parentUuid": "b95431ba_96c3a240",
      "revId": "e2c0a1dd1f0192633101ffbab1839d1636ff2c51",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
    {
